description:
Enable AI agents and automated tests to authenticate quickly by using Noos's dev-login endpoint.

## Options
1. **Direct usage** - Document that agents can call Noos dev-login directly and use the returned JWT
2. **Proxy endpoint** - Add `POST /api/auth/dev-login` that proxies to Noos

## Implementation (if proxy)
```typescript
// POST /api/auth/dev-login
router.post('/dev-login', async (req, res) => {
  if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production') {
    return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Disabled in production' });
  }
  const noosRes = await fetch(`${NOOS_URL}/api/auth/dev-login`, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({ email: req.body.email })
  });
  const data = await noosRes.json();
  res.json(data);
});
```

## Note
OpenChat-ip2 (closed) was for manual token paste. This ticket is for programmatic dev-login.

